    "solution": "The Eastern and Western regions of Nigeria achieved the status of self-government in 1957.\n\nWestern Region: Attained self-government on August 8, 1957, under the leadership of Chief Obafemi Awolowo.\n\nEastern Region: Followed shortly after, gaining self-government on October 1, 1957, led by Dr. Nnamdi Azikiwe.\n\nThis milestone was part of Nigeria's gradual decolonization process under British rule, culminating in the country's full independence on October 1, 1960. The Northern Region achieved self-government later, in 1959, due to its more cautious approach to political reforms.",
