    },
    "section": "",
    "image": "",
    "answer": "c",
    "solution": "The primary issue undermining Nigeria’s population censuses is political manipulation by elites. Political and ethnic leaders often inflate or suppress population figures to secure advantages such as:\n\nResource Allocation: Federal revenue and infrastructure projects are distributed based on population size, incentivizing states to overreport numbers.\n\nElectoral Advantage: Larger populations translate to more legislative seats and political influence, driving falsification.\n\nEthnic and Regional Rivalry: Competing groups manipulate data to assert dominance, fostering distrust in census outcomes.",
    "examtype": "utme",
