    "id": 1390,
    "question": "The British colonial rule in Nigeria brought about",
    "option": {
      "a": "stagnationin social formations",
      "b": "the pampering of traditional rulers",
      "c": "a change in the mode of production",
      "d": "stabilization in the price of raw materials"
    },
    "section": "",
    "image": "",
    "answer": "c",
    "solution": "British colonial rule fundamentally altered Nigeria’s economic structure by replacing subsistence agriculture and local trade with a cash-crop and extractive economy geared toward global markets. Key changes included:\n\nIntroduction of Cash Crops: Palm oil, cocoa, and groundnuts were prioritized for export, disrupting traditional subsistence practices.\n\nMonetization and Wage Labor: Shifted from barter systems to wage-based labor, integrating Nigeria into global capitalism.\n\nResource Extraction: Exploitation of minerals (e.g., tin, coal) and infrastructure (railways) built to serve colonial economic interests.",
    "examtype": "utme",
    "examyear": "2008"
  },
